# Cursor Rules - Cursor for PMs

## Project Type
MERN + Gemini AI + Bull/Redis

## Critical Rules

### 1. NEVER Break Existing Code
- BEFORE changing any file, check what it does
- ASK me: "This changes [file]. OK?"
- Keep all existing functions working
- Add new code, don't delete old without asking

### 2. File Creation Rules
- Frontend: React functional components only
- Backend: Express routes in routes/, logic in services/
- Models: Mongoose schemas only
- AI: Each agent in separate file under agents/

### 3. Code Standards
- Use async/await, no .then()
- Error handling in all try/catch
- No console.log in production code
- Environment variables from .env only

### 4. Database
- MongoDB for all data
- GridFS for audio/video files
- Index all query fields

### 5. When to Ask
Ask before:
- Changing any working feature
- Adding new dependencies
- Changing folder structure
- Modifying AI prompts

Don't ask for:
- Basic syntax
- Standard patterns
- Minor fixes
